# What I Learned

This room helped me understand that port scanning isn't just about typing `nmap <target>` and waiting for results. Different scan types have different purposes.

A TCP Connect Scan is simple and works without special privileges, but it's also the easiest to detect. TCP SYN Scan is much faster and quieter, which is why it's commonly used during penetration testing. UDP scans are slower because UDP doesn't respond the same way TCP does, but they're still important for discovering services like DNS and SNMP.

Overall, this room gave me a much better understanding of how Nmap communicates with a target and how choosing the right scan can save time while collecting better information.


